56.9	Pete_Best	Pete Best	Pete Best (born 24 November 1941) is a British musician, best known as the original drummer in The Beatles. He was born in the city of Madras, then part of British India. After moving from India to Liverpool in 1945, Best's mother, Mona Best (1924â€“1988), opened The Casbah Coffee Club in the cellar of the Bests' large house in Liverpool, which became very popular with a membership list of over a thousand. The Beatles (then known as The Quarrymen) played some of their first concerts at the club. Best played there with his first band, The Black Jacks, and later with The Beatles.	http://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/4/4c/Pete_Best_drumming.jpg/220px-Pete_Best_drumming.jpg
